{"id":5459,"date":"2019-08-16T20:41:10","date_gmt":"2019-08-16T20:41:10","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/?page_id=5459"},"modified":"2021-06-01T20:16:51","modified_gmt":"2021-06-01T20:16:51","slug":"treatment-approach-and-methodology","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/treatment-approach-and-methodology\/","title":{"rendered":"Treatment Approach and Methodology"},"content":{"rendered":"<section class=\"ffb-id-3agqhga8 fg-section fg-text-dark\"><div class=\"fg-container container fg-container-large fg-container-lvl--1 \"><div class=\"fg-row row    \" ><div class=\"ffb-id-1425711854 fg-col col-xs-12 col-md-12 fg-text-dark\"><p class=\"ffb-id-3agqhkcl fg-paragraph text-left    fg-text-dark\">\n<p>Given that each person is unique, there are a multitude of treatment approaches and solutions offered to accommodate a person&#8217;s beliefs, their particular dependence and other possible concerns that may be necessary to resolve. For example, if you were agnostic, you would probably feel miserable in a recovery program that puts heavy emphasis on Christian values. The same idea pertains to those with a holistic lifestyle, they might feel uneasy with a substance replacement program because they wish to rehabilitate themselves in a natural way. At Pathways Real Life Recovery, we cater each treatment program to suit your unique wants and needs.<\/p>\n<h4>We&#8217;re here to help 24\/7! Call <a href=\"tel:14352872700\">(435) 287-2700<\/a> Today!<\/h4>\n<p><img style=\"margin: 0px 0px 15px 15px\" title=\"Our Treatment Methods and Principles of Successful Treatment - Pathways Real Life Recovery\" src=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/effective-treatment.jpg\" alt=\"Embracing Life - Pathways Real Life Recovery - Addiction and Rehab Recovery Services in Utah\" align=\"right\" \/><\/p>\n<h2>Principles of Successful Treatment<\/h2>\n<p>30 years of research has proven that to defeat addiction, avoid relapse, and make life long recovery a reality, there are a number of important factors. The following key principles are the basis of any successful treatment program:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>No one treatment will work for everyone.<\/li>\n<li>Access to treatment should be readily available.<\/li>\n<li>Addiction is a complex but treatable condition that has the ability to affect behaviors and healthy brain function.<\/li>\n<li>Effective treatment addresses the root cause of addiction, as well as other possible mental disorders, and not just the symptom of<\/li>\n<li>drug use. Treatment should help a person be healthy in mind and body.<\/li>\n<li>Staying in treatment long enough is critical to success.<\/li>\n<li>Counseling and other behavioral therapies are the most commonly used forms of treatment.<\/li>\n<li>Medications are often an important part of treatment, especially when combined with behavioral therapies.<\/li>\n<li>Treatment plans should be regularly reviewed and modified to fit a person&rsquo;s changing needs.<\/li>\n<li>Medically assisted detoxification is only the first stage of treatment.<\/li>\n<li>Treatment doesn&#8217;t need to be voluntary to be effective.<\/li>\n<li>Drug use during treatment must be monitored continuously.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2>Treatment Methods at Pathways Real Life Recovery<\/h2>\n<p>A trained professional will perform an evaluation to determine what mixture of treatments will be effective for your needs and symptoms.<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/group-therapy\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Group Therapy<\/span><\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"\/cognitive-behavioral-therapy\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Cognitive Behavioral<\/span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Therapy<\/span><\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/recreational-therapy\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Experiential Therapy<\/span><\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/changing-core-beliefs-emotional-reactions-behaviors\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Changing Core Beliefs<\/span><\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/relapse-prevention-utah\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Relapse Prevention<\/span><\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/vocational-and-educational-services-utah\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Vocational and Educational<\/span><\/a> Training<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/sober-recovery-companion-utah\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Sober Companion<\/span><\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/detox-center-utah\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Detox<\/span><\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/addiction-aftercare-in-utah\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Addiction Aftercare<\/span><\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/art-and-music-therapy\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Art \/ Music Health Therapy<\/span><\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/belief-restructuring\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Belief Restructuring<\/span><\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"\/nad-iv-therapy-in-utah\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">NAD-IV Therapy<\/span><\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/treatment-approach-and-methodology\/dialectical-behavior-therapy-in-utah\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Dialectical Behavior Therapy<\/span><\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>Call <a href=\"tel:14352872700\">(435) 287-2700<\/a> to schedule a FREE Consultation.<\/h4>\n<\/p><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/section><style><\/style><script type=\"text\/javascript\"><\/script>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"author":3,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":[],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v16.8 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>